<h1 id="covid-19-in-hong-kong">Covid-19 in Hong Kong</h1>

<p>As I am currently living in Hong Kong. Since the spread of COVID-19 near the end of January, more than 100 countries are infected. This made all the schools closed and holiday extension. I am not complaninig about the extra few days of holidays, but not able to go outside freely sucks.</p>

<p>Many schools including mine has started online school with tools like zoom, google hangout just to name a few. At first, I felt overwhelmed of all the homework and assignment piling up. Especially my exam in May is coming soon, teachers gave us extra work to catchup. It was very tiring and made me feel <strong>SchoolSick</strong>. (I know it may sound weird)</p>

<h1 id="staying-at-home">Staying at Home</h1>

<p>Due to the outbreak, we had to stay at home. Usually on Saturdays and Sundays I go to church and join some extra activies to fill up my time. But now all of them are cancelled üò¢.</p>

<h2 id="tips-to-be-less-bored">Tips to be LESS BORED</h2>

<p>Below are some methods I tried over the <em>stay-at-home</em> period.</p>

<h3 id="1-find-a-project-to-do">1. Find a project to do</h3>

